OL,3,CWater bosses keep 'close eye' on
OL,4,CSomerset reservoir levels among lowest
OL,5,Cin UK
OL,7,FWater bosses in the South West are
OL,8,Fkeeping "a very close eye" on
OL,9,Freservoir levels in Somerset, which
OL,10,Fare among some of the lowest in the UK.
OL,12,FDrought officials have today warned
OL,13,Fthat England is now suffering from
OL,14,F"nationally significant" water
OL,15,Fshortfalls, with high temperatures and
OL,16,Fdry weather set to continue this week.
OL,18,FReservoir levels in Somerset are
OL,19,Fsignificantly lower than this time
OL,20,Flast year, with Chew Valley, Blagdon
OL,21,Fand Cheddar among the worst hit.
